Connected Devices Privacy Notice
Last updated: February 2024
At SharkNinja, we exist to deliver on our mission of “positively impacting people’s lives, every day in every home, around the world” This includes doing everything possible to protect your privacy and secure your personal information.
When you download our Mobile Apps, you can control and monitor your Shark or Ninja digitally connected device using your phone or any other compatible device.
This Privacy Notice aims to inform you about how we collect, use, disclose, and store personal information when you:
Use Shark or Ninja connected devices
Use any mobile application (the “App”) that supports these products.
Participate in a research survey or product test.
Contact us and we respond to your requests or questions.
Signup to receive marketing communications or offers.
What is a digitally connected device?
A digitally connected device is an electronic device that is connected to other devices or networks via wireless protocols such as Bluetooth, Wi-Fi.
Who is responsible for your personal information?
SharkNinja is responsible for determining “why” and “how” your personal information is collected. To be able to deliver our services we also determine which approved companies we share your personal information with.  All these companies are bound by an obligation to implement appropriate security measures and have specific contractual terms on “how” and “when” they are allowed to use your personal information on our behalf.
What personal information do we collect and why?
We collect, hold, and process your personal information in accordance with the applicable data protection laws as follows: SharkNinja Europe Ltd and SharkNinja Operating LLC operate as joint data controllers.
